'''Irreligion in Kenya''' is uncommon among Kenyans, as [[Christianity]] is the predominant faith. Only 0.4% of Kenyans claim [[Irreligion|no religion]].<ref>{{cite news|title= The rise of atheism in modern Kenya|publisher= [[Daily Nation]]|date=|url= http://www.nation.co.ke/Features/DN2/The-rise-and-rise-of-nons/-/957860/1901662/-/cvmtnx/-/index.html|accessdate=2013-07-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Why We Don't Believe In God|publisher= [[The Star (Kenya)|The Star]]|date= |url= http://www.the-star.co.ke/news/article-128332/why-we-dont-believe-god|accessdate= 2013-08-23|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130821130236/http://www.the-star.co.ke/news/article-128332/why-we-dont-believe-god|archivedate= 2013-08-21|df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= What Kenyans think about Atheism|publisher= [[The Standard (Kenya)|Standard]]|url=https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/mobile/ktn/watch/2000077573/what-kenyans-think-about-atheism|accessdate=2013-08-24}}</ref> [[Atheism]] is greatly stigmatized in [[Kenya]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Atheism Not Against Kenya's Constitution|publisher= [[The Star (Kenya)|The Star]]|url=http://www.the-star.co.ke/news/article-173994/atheism-not-against-kenyas-constitution|accessdate=2013-08-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Atheism is greatly misunderstood in Kenya|publisher= [[Daily Nation]]|url=http://mobile.nation.co.ke/blogs/Atheism-greatly-misunderstood-in-Kenya/-/1949942/2326304/-/format/xhtml/-/11ftuurz/-/index.html|accessdate=2013-08-24}}</ref>

[[Harrison Mumia]] set up one of the first atheist group in Kenya and was denied the right to be recognized officially by the government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/the-conversation-africa/atheist-group-in-kenya-te_b_10253694.html|title=Atheist group in Kenya tests boundaries of religious tolerance|first=The Conversation|last=Africa|date=2 June 2016|publisher=|accessdate=18 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/lifestyle/article/2000198476/god-does-not-exist-in-mumia-s-world|title=God does not exist in Harrison Mumia's world|first=Josaya|last=Wasonga|publisher=|accessdate=18 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/ureport/story/2000200486/who-is-afraid-of-atheism-in-kenya|title=ureport Your Story|publisher=|accessdate=18 February 2017}}</ref>

